==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[eradicatus]]'', the past participle of ''[[eradicare]]'', from ''[[e-#Latin|e-]]'', "out", + ''[[radix]]'' (root: ''[[radic-]]''), "root".
===Verb===
{{en-verb|eradicate|eradicates|eradicated|eradicating}}
#{{transitive}} To [[pull]] [[up]] by the [[root]]s; to [[completely]] [[destroy]]; to put an [[end]] to.
